<paragraph id="7E177C16FFB6FFA4EBC7629E906E17CF" blockId="37.[140,1095,133,731]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">
<emphasis id="4CDCA004FFB6FFA4EBC7629E933016CE" box="[179,577,197,221]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="B9A80795FFB6FFA4EA4C629E933016CE" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1919" box="[312,577,197,221]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Hesperophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tectum">Hesperophyllum tectum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is known only from the original description and a subsequent re-description by 
<bibRefCitation id="1A3901E7FFB6FFA4E94762BE93BE16EE" author="BANSE, K." box="[563,719,229,253]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" pagination="191 - 222" refId="ref17967" refString="BANSE, K., 1972, On some species of Phyllodocidae, Syllidae, Nephtyidae, Goniadidae, Apistobranchidae, and Spionidae (Polychaeta) from the northeast Paci  c Ocean, Paci  c Science, 26, 191 - 222." type="journal article" year="1972">Banse (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus id="A113C2B4FFB6FFA4E87B62BE924E16EE" box="[783,831,229,253]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">type</typeStatus>
material consists of a slide with a single parapodium. The combination of a dorsal acicula and a capillary chaeta, the broad dorsal cirrus, the ventral cirrus with the longitudinal axis obliquely orientated, and the rostrum of chaetal shafts with a large number of teeth, shows that it belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="B9A80795FFB6FFA4EA27633E9090176E" authorityName="Kato &amp; Pleijel" authorityYear="2002" box="[339,481,357,381]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Notophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4CDCA004FFB6FFA4EA27633E9090176E" box="[339,481,357,381]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">Notophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The attened, rather than in ated, ventral tentacular cirri described by Chamberlin may constitute a unique feature within 
<taxonomicName id="B9A80795FFB6FFA4E8DB63DF954C178F" authorityName="Kato &amp; Pleijel" authorityYear="2002" box="[943,1085,388,412]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Notophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4CDCA004FFB6FFA4E8DB63DF954C178F" box="[943,1085,388,412]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">Notophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but must be veried by further investigation of additional specimens from the 
<typeStatus id="A113C2B4FFB6FFA4EBF8639E91CC17CE" box="[140,189,453,477]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E177C16FFB6FFA4EBC763BF923E1488" blockId="37.[140,1095,133,731]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">
<bibRefCitation id="1A3901E7FFB6FFA4EBC763BF902C17EF" author="BANSE, K." box="[179,349,484,508]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" pagination="191 - 222" refId="ref17967" refString="BANSE, K., 1972, On some species of Phyllodocidae, Syllidae, Nephtyidae, Goniadidae, Apistobranchidae, and Spionidae (Polychaeta) from the northeast Paci  c Ocean, Paci  c Science, 26, 191 - 222." type="journal article" year="1972">Banse’s (1972)</bibRefCitation>
redescription was based on a specimen (
<accessionNumber id="61FBE1F5FFB6FFA4E84863BF92B717EF" box="[828,966,484,508]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/MCZ19663" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">
<collectionCode id="18B9E4D3FFB6FFA4E84863BF920A17EF" box="[828,891,484,508]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" type="Museum">MCZ</collectionCode>
19663
</accessionNumber>
) from 
<collectingRegion id="BC6CB2F4FFB6FFA4EF6863BF91B3140F" country="Philippines" name="San Juan" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">San Juan</collectingRegion>
Islands, 
<collectingRegion id="BC6CB2F4FFB6FFA4EA40605F90CB140F" box="[308,442,516,540]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">Washington</collectingRegion>
, in addition to the 
<typeStatus id="A113C2B4FFB6FFA4E9C0605E9392140E" box="[692,739,517,541]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">type</typeStatus>
. Our examination of Banse’s specimen indicates that it belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="B9A80795FFB6FFA4E94B607F9282142F" authority="Moore, 1906" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1906" box="[575,1011,548,572]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Notophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="imbricatum">
<emphasis id="4CDCA004FFB6FFA4E94B607F9227142F" box="[575,854,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">Notophyllum imbricatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1A3901E7FFB6FFA4E815607E9282142F" author="MOORE, J. P." box="[865,1011,548,572]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" pagination="217 - 260" refId="ref19459" refString="MOORE, J. P., 1906, Additional new species of Polychaeta from the north Paci  c, Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 58, 217 - 260." type="journal article" year="1906">Moore, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the presence of unique proboscoideal hook-shaped papillae. The ventral tentacular cirri of Banse’s specimen has the normal, asymmetrical shape present in other 
<taxonomicName id="B9A80795FFB6FFA4EBF860D8906B1488" authorityName="Kato &amp; Pleijel" authorityYear="2002" box="[140,282,643,667]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Notophyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4CDCA004FFB6FFA4EBF860D8906B1488" box="[140,282,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">Notophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and are in ated, rather than attened as stated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E177C16FFB6FFA4EBC760F8905914C8" blockId="37.[140,1095,133,731]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">
As 
<taxonomicName id="B9A80795FFB6FFA4EBAA60FF902114A8" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1919" box="[222,336,676,699]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Hesperophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tectum">
<emphasis id="4CDCA004FFB6FFA4EBAA60FF902114A8" box="[222,336,676,699]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1171">H. tectum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently insu ciently known, we refer to it as 
